# UI Improvements & Screen Dimmer Plan

## Context

Single-screen Expo radio app. Layout: Header → ControlPanel → CategoryTabs → StationList.
Playback via `useRadioPlayer()` / `RadioPlayerService`. Hook signal: `playerState.isPlaying`.
`expo-keep-awake` active while playing (screen stays on, playback stable on Galaxy).
Screen dimming via **in-app overlay only** — `expo-brightness` was tried and reverted.

## UI Improvement 1: Pinned Mini Player Bar ✅ DONE

**Problem:** ControlPanel scrolls off-screen when browsing the station list.

**Completed:**
- `components/MiniPlayerBar.tsx` — pinned to bottom inside `SafeAreaView`, visible when `currentStation` is set
- Shows station name, episode title (podcasts), status, play/pause, stop
- Reuses `togglePlayPause` and `stop` from `App.tsx`
- Bottom safe area via `useSafeAreaInsets()` from `react-native-safe-area-context` (required for Android `edgeToEdgeEnabled`)

**Optional later:** Expandable volume or dim-mode indicator

## UI Improvement 2: Finish i18n in ControlPanel ✅ DONE

**Problem:** ControlPanel uses hardcoded Korean (`연결 중...`, `볼륨`) while other components use `useLanguage()`.

**Completed:**
- `useLanguage()` wired into `ControlPanel.tsx`
- Loading and volume labels use `t.loading`, `t.volume`
- Play/pause/stop buttons use `t.play`, `t.pause`, `t.stop` as accessibility labels

**Follow-up (optional):** Map `RadioPlayerService` error messages through i18n in the UI layer

## Feature: Screen Dim via Overlay After 10 Seconds ✅ DONE

**Goal:** After 10 continuous seconds of playback, dim screen visually. Audio continues. Tap restores and resets timer.

**Approach:** In-app overlay only (does not change system brightness; minimal battery savings)

**Completed:**
- `hooks/useScreenDimmer.ts` — 10s timer (3s in `__DEV__`), gated on `isPlaying && !isLoading`
- `components/ScreenDimOverlay.tsx` — full-screen `rgba(0,0,0,0.7)` overlay (~30% perceived brightness)
- Transparent tap layer with hint; tap calls `wake()` to dismiss overlay
- Wired in `App.tsx`; i18n via `screenDimmedHint` (`탭하여 화면 켜기` / `Tap to wake screen`)
- `PlayerKeepAwake` active during playback — dimming and keep-awake coexist

**Note:** Overlay blocks UI interaction while dimmed; does not turn screen off.

## Behavior Matrix

| Event | Action |
|-------|--------|
| `isPlaying && !isLoading` | Start 10s timer |
| Timer fires | Show dim overlay |
| User taps | Hide overlay, restart timer if still playing |
| Pause / Stop | Clear timer, remove overlay |
| Station switch while playing | Reset timer |
| App backgrounded | Clear overlay (restart timer on foreground if still playing) |

## Implementation Order

1. ~~i18n in ControlPanel~~ ✅ Done
2. ~~MiniPlayerBar~~ ✅ Done
3. ~~useScreenDimmer + ScreenDimOverlay~~ ✅ Done (overlay-only)

## Out of Scope / Tried & Reverted

- `expo-brightness` — tested on Galaxy S25; app/system brightness unreliable; reverted to overlay-only
- Removing `keep-awake` for screen auto-off — caused playback to stop on Galaxy background
- Centralized theme / dark mode
- Lock-screen now playing controls
- User-configurable dim delay

## Known Limitations

- `isLoading` flicker during stream buffering may reset dim timer
- Overlay dims app UI only; backlight stays on (`keep-awake`)
- Plan opacity: adjust `backgroundColor` in `ScreenDimOverlay.tsx` (currently `0.7`)
